======================================================
04_01_general_summary.sql - DESCRIPTION
======================================================

Description:
This SQL script provides a unified summary of the entire
dataset by combining multiple key statistics into a
single output table.

It builds on the initial exploration (01) by organizing
all general metrics into a compact and structured format
that is easier to export and analyze.

The goal is to understand:
- the overall size and structure of the dataset
- the scoring behavior across matches
- how match results are distributed
- and the level of match intensity through card data

------------------------------------------------------
Structure of the Script
------------------------------------------------------

The script is organized as a single query using UNION ALL,
where each row represents a different metric.

It includes:
- dataset overview (matches, teams, seasons)
- date range (first and last match)
- goal statistics and scoring distribution
- match outcomes and their percentages
- card-related metrics

------------------------------------------------------
CSV Output Description (01_all.csv)
------------------------------------------------------

The output of this script is a summary table where each
row represents a specific metric and its corresponding
value.

This file serves as a general overview of the dataset and
acts as a foundation for the rest of the project.

It is designed to be simple, readable, and suitable for
quick inspection and basic visualization in Python.